The alignment of the layout.
The wrapping of the layout.

This API is obsolete.
For information about how to develop ASP.NET mobile applications, see the [www.asp.net/mobile](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkID=182900) Web site.

This constructor looks first to the specified `style` for the values of its <xref:System.Web.UI.MobileControls.Adapters.WmlMobileTextWriter.WmlLayout.Align%2A> and <xref:System.Web.UI.MobileControls.Adapters.WmlMobileTextWriter.WmlLayout.Wrap%2A> properties.
If these properties are not set in the `style`, this constructor uses the corresponding properties from the specified `currentLayout`.
The style to use as a base for this layout.
The layout to use as a base for this layout.
Sets or returns the alignment.
The default value is <xref href="System.Web.UI.MobileControls.Alignment.NotSet"></xref>.
This API is obsolete.
For information about how to develop ASP.NET mobile applications, see the [www.asp.net/mobile](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkID=182900) Web site.
The <xref:System.Web.UI.MobileControls.Adapters.WmlMobileTextWriter.WmlLayout.Align%2A> property can be set to any <xref:System.Web.UI.MobileControls.Alignment> value.
An enumerated value representing the alignment of the layout.

Compares a <xref href="System.Web.UI.MobileControls.Adapters.WmlMobileTextWriter.WmlLayout"></xref> object to the current <xref href="System.Web.UI.MobileControls.Adapters.WmlMobileTextWriter.WmlLayout"></xref> object.

For information about how to develop ASP.NET mobile applications, see the [www.asp.net/mobile](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkID=182900) Web site.
The <xref:System.Web.UI.MobileControls.Adapters.WmlMobileTextWriter.WmlLayout.Compare%2A> method is called internally by the <xref:System.Web.UI.MobileControls.Adapters.WmlMobileTextWriter> class.
The layout object to compare.

`true` if the values for <xref href="System.Web.UI.MobileControls.Adapters.WmlMobileTextWriter.WmlLayout.Wrap"></xref> and <xref href="System.Web.UI.MobileControls.Adapters.WmlMobileTextWriter.WmlLayout.Align"></xref> are the same in both layouts; otherwise, `false`.
Sets or returns the specified wrapping mode for the style.
The default value is <xref href="System.Web.UI.MobileControls.Wrapping.NotSet"></xref>.
This API is obsolete.
For information about how to develop ASP.NET mobile applications, see the [www.asp.net/mobile](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkID=182900) Web site.
The <xref:System.Web.UI.MobileControls.Adapters.WmlMobileTextWriter.WmlLayout.Wrap%2A> property can be set to any <xref:System.Web.UI.MobileControls.Wrapping> value.
The specified wrapping mode for the style.
